xperience the strange phenomenon of going uphill when your vehicle&rsquo;s engine is turned off.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 4&nbsp;&nbsp; Jeju - Gimpo - Gangwondo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; T</span><span>ake domestic flights from Jeju to Gimpo Domestic airport.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span>Experience Kimchi making,</span></strong><span> fresh Ginseng juice<strong> </strong>and <strong>trying out Korea traditional Costumes</strong> for picture taking.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><span>Take a ferry to <strong>Nami Island</strong> the symbolic backdrop of mega hit Korean drama &ldquo;Winter Sonata&rdquo;. You can feel the excitement of the romantic drama and take a walk down beautiful tree-lined paths with your loved ones featured in the most memorable scenes. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span>-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>Great experience to enjoy <strong>hot spring</strong> facility in the resort rich with mineral. It not only can healing the body and mind.*( Pse bring along swimming suits and cap )<strong></strong></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 5&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo-Yongin&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Seoraksan</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> is the third highest mountain in South Korea. <strong>Bronze Buddha of Sinheungsa</strong>. (Buddhist Temple) in Seoraksan National Park.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Drop by <strong>Teddy Bear Farm </strong>where is display at the garden and gallery.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proceed to <strong>Daepohang Fish Market</strong> where you can taste the fresh sashimi own expense</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 6&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo &ndash; Seoul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n