></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">(Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong><strong></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shop by the <strong>Ginseng Outlet, Liverin outlet,&nbsp; Duty Free cosmetic shop &amp; Amethyst Factory</strong></span><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">.</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Snap photo at<strong> Love Lock desk at N-Tower</strong></span><strong><span>, </span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">shooting place for 2014 hits Korea drama <em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;My Love From The Star&rdquo; </span></em>. <em>*( Excluded N-Tower Observatory desk )</em></span><strong></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shopping at <strong>Myeondong Fashion Street</strong>, a major shopping district lined with shops selling quality-branded goods .</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 8&nbsp;&nbsp; INCHEON / KUALA LUMPUR / KUCHING&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast<em>)</em>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">D7507 ICN/KUL 1115-1700</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK5228 KUL/KCH 1920-2105</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span>-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span>Local Food Product Shop</span></strong><span> for purchasing some authentic Korean local products.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Transfer to the airport</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> for your flight back home</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQUENCE OF ITINERARY SUBJECT TO LOCAL ARRANGEMENT</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" align=\"center\"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Special Meals included</strong>:</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraph\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Breakfast will serve American Breakfast or Chinese cum Local Korean Style. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Lunch &amp; Dinner: Jeju Black Pork Bulgogi, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Seafood Steamboat, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Chinese Style Meal 5dishes + 1soup, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Korean style Pork BBQ X 2 Times, Ginseng Chicken</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Soup + Ginseng Wine + Noodle</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">, Bimbibap + steamboat</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Dalgabi, Mushroom Steamboat</span><em></em></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Accommodations:</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(2N) Jeju Palace Hotel / Jeju Hawaii Hotel or similar</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1N) Sorak Pine Resort or similar</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1N) Yanji Pine Resort or similar</span></p><p>(2N) Co-op Omogiok Residence or similar</p>'),
(114, 'photo/5302d8944230f.jpg', 'PSTT02 Semenggoh Wildlife Centre ', 1, ' Half day - Minimum 2Pax', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Semenggoh Orang Utan Rehabilitation Centre is a centre that serves as rehabilitation centre for orphan orang utans. The centre offers a rare opportunity to be close range with the &lsquo;Wild Man of Borneo&rsquo;. The centre provides a perfect natural habitat to observe the natural behavior of this primate. Here, young Orang Utans, who were either orphaned or rescued from captivity, are trained to survive in the wild. See the Orang Utans wondering in towering trees of the untouched rainforest before coming down for feeding. Feeding times is at 0900hrs &amp; 1500hrs daily.<em></em></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">*Please note that wild nature does not perform on demand. We search for glimpse of them in their natural environment and may or may not succeed.</span></span></em></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\"><span lang=\"ZH-TW\"></span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span><span lang=\"ZH-TW\"></span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span><span lang=\"ZH-TW\"></span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span>0900hrs<span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span>1500hrs<span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span></span></span></em></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Tour Duration : Half Day</span></span></strong></p>'),
(140, 'photo/5922963e59e71.jpg', 'PSTT03 Annah Rais Longhouse', 1, ' Half day-Minimum 2pax', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Annah Rais Longhouse still preserved its traditional look. Bidayuh, the second largest ethnic group in Sarawak, is formerly known as the &lsquo;Land Dayak&rsquo; and was once also known as the &lsquo;Engineer of Bamboo&rsquo;. You will be able to see the splendid architecture of their longhouse which was build mostly by bamboo. During the visit, you can view the villagers with their own daily routine like rice pounding and winnowing, basket and mat weaving, bamboo carving and many else. You will be brought into the most unique and important structure, the &lsquo;Baruk&rsquo;, or the head house which is situated in the middle of the longhouse. This once used as a fort to protect the whole village from being attack by enemy. Inside the &lsquo;Baruk&rsquo;, you will be able to view the real human skulls hanging </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">around the fire place in the middle and also their sacred war drum. </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Tour Duration: Half Day</span></span></strong></p>'),
(113, 'photo/59229687a28c5.jpg', 'PSTT04 Sarawak Cultural Village', 1, 'Half Day - Min. 2 Person', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Sarawak Cultural Village. Popularly known as the &ldquo;Living Museum&rsquo;, the Village is a showcase of kaleidoscope of Sarawak&rsquo;s cultures and traditions. On arrival, you will explore the 7 authentic replicas of ethnic houses; Chinese Farm House, Malay Stilted House, Melanau Tall House, Penan Hut as well Longhouse of the Iban, Bidayuh and Orang Ulu. Displayed in each houses are the many artifacts made by the individual dwellers. </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Demonstration of arts and crafts like beadwork, wood and bamboo carvings, &lsquo;Pua&rsquo; and straw weaving can be seenwhile touring the Village. You also will be entertained with 45 minutes of the traditional dances of the various ethnic tribes of Sarawak at the Village theatre. Shows are fixed daily at 1130hrs &ndash; 1215hrs and 1600hrs &ndash; 1645hrs<strong>.</strong></span></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">&ldquo;<span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span>&rdquo;<span lang=\"ZH-CN\"></span></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\"><br /></span></span></strong></span></span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Tour Duration: Half Day</span></span></span></strong></p>'),
(112, 'photo/5302d713014bb.jpg', 'Kuching - Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse', 0, 'Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse (Half Day) (Min 2 Person)', '<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"heading4\">Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse</span><span class=\"contentArial-red\"><br />Half Day&nbsp;Min 2 Person&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><br /><span class=\"contentArial-red\">Description</span><br /></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Located about 70km from Kuching, This bidayuh longhouse Anah Rais, still preserved its traditional look. They stayed in a house made from well preserved bamboo which is called Longhouse. Here guest can view and walk on the unique architectural and cultural features of longhouse and traditional farming lifestyle of the Bidayuh peoples. They built imposing octagonal skull houses ( BARUK )&nbsp; to house they enemy&rsquo;s head. The original longhouse is over a century old and many biliks are now vacant as the younger generation move to the towns and cities in search of work and education. Visit with some of the older folks and learn their traditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span class=\"contentArial-red\">Includes</span></strong><br /></span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">- Tours as per itinerary&nbsp;<br />- Transportation&nbsp;<br />- Entrance Fees&nbsp;<br />- English, Malay or Mandarin Speaking Guide</span></span></span></span></span></p>'),
