(124, 'photo/551b681d28e5d.jpg', 'Philippines 1', 1, '5D4N Boracay Island - including Helmet Diving, Flying Fish & ATV', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">5 DAYS 4 NIGHTS BORACAY ISLAND</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">DAY 1&nbsp; KUCHING / KUALA LUMPUR&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AK5215 KCH/KUL 1910-2100</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Flight departure to Kuala Lumpur. Check in KLIA2 Hotel and rest.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 2</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>KUALA LUMPUR / </span></strong><strong><span>KALIBO&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (LOB/D)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK608 KUL/KLO 1040-1435</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Upon arrival at Kalibo Airport, meet and transfer to jetty (approx. 2 hrs). Take 20-min ferry ride to</span><span> the beautiful </span><span>Boracay Island. Then transfer to hotel check in. </span><span>Free at own leisure.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span><br /></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 3</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp; Boracay Island Hopping &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>After breakfast, depart for Boracay Island Hopping (4hrs), enjoy the exciting Helmet Diving and Flying Fish. Afternoon, proceed to Discovery Tunnel by ATV.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 4</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp; Kalibo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Full day free at own leisure. (</span><span>Guests can </span><span>join optional tours with own expenses).</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 5</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>DEPARTURE </span></strong><strong><span>KALIBO&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>(B)</span></strong><strong></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK609 KLO/KUL 1505-1850&nbsp;&nbsp; AK5214 KUL/KCH 2115-2305</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Check out and t</span><span>ransfer to airport for the flight departure </span><span>back home</span><span>. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4* Hotel used: Boracay Regency Resort</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">** The sequence of the itinerary may varies on the actual tour without notice&nbsp;</span></strong></p>'),
(125, 'photo/5514bbac866bc.jpg', 'Philippines 2', 1, '5D4N Cebu + Bohol Island ', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">5 DAYS 4 NIGHTS CEBU + BOHOL ISLAND</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Cebu is the trading center of Southeast Asia in the 13th century. Discovered by&nbsp;Ferdinand Magellan on April 8, 1521. Rich of its pre-Hispanic relics, pre-historic past, antiques, and artifacts that have been found in different parts of the island. Cebu now is the gateway of central and southern Philippines and is the country&#39;s favorite tourist destination.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><a href=\"https://www.google.com.my/imgres?imgurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.markmaranga.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2010%2F06%2FDSC_3448a.jpg&amp;imgrefurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.markmaranga.com%2Fmagellans-cross-a-symbol-of-cebu%2F&amp;docid=DczJQPYNNB8HnM&amp;tbnid=TFnBLPJ5AAV-CM%3A&amp;w=720&amp;h=480&amp;ei=l7j2VOrKOYewuASfhYF4&amp;ved=0CAIQxiAwAA&amp;iact=c\"><span lang=\"EN-MY\"> </span></a></span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">DAY 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KUCHING / KOTA KINABALU AK6354 1340-1505</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">KOTA KINABALU / CEBU Z2132 1800-1955</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Flight departure to Cebu via Kota Kinabalu. Upon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 2</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>CEBU CITY TOUR &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B/L)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">After breakfast, start the tour with Cebu City. Visit to <strong>Fort San Pedro</strong> (first Spanish fort build in Philippines), <strong>Magellans Shrine</strong> (Ferdinard Magellan planted a cross in the island of Cebu April 8 1521,now the island&#39;s famous landmark), <strong>Basilica Minore del Sto.Nino</strong> (Cebu&#39;s oldest Roman Catholic Church, also still retains the original stone texture and natural color it had in 1735). Evening time free at own leisure (guests can enjoy shopping spree at Ayala Shopping Mall).</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CEBU &ndash; TAGBILARAN (BOHOL)&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B</span></strong><strong><span>/L</span></strong><strong><span>)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Early morning, transfer to Cebu Ferry Port for the ride to <strong>Tagbilaran</strong> (Bohol). Meet and Greet by Bohol tour guide, then proceed with Bohol Countryside tour. Places include </span><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Chocolate Hills,&nbsp;Man-Made Forest,&nbsp;Tarsier Encounter,&nbsp;River Cruise with Buffet Lunch,&nbsp;Baclayon Church &amp; Museum,&nbsp;Blood Compact Site,&nbsp;Clarin Ancestral Houses</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TAGBILARAN (BOHOL) - CEBU</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>(B/L)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Transfer back to Cebu by ferry. Meet the guide and proceed for <strong>Cebu Island Hopping</strong> tour with lunch.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Check-in Hotel and free at own leisure. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span>DAY 5</span></strong><strong><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><