(136, 'photo/592292f08d4fd.jpg', 'PSTT05 Wind Cave & Fairy Cave', 1, '& Half day-Minimum 2 pax', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Fairy Caves and Wind Caves, about 50 minutes drives from Kuching City. The Fairy Cave is about 3 storeys high. After a quick clib through the cave with tocrchlights, the cave opens up into a main chamber. Sunlight streams into the chamber, enabling you to view the limestone formation of several types. View the beautiful and some eerie shape of nature creations, the stalactites and stalagmites. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">There is a formation that has been likened to the Godness of Mercy which at about 3 meters in height resembles a woman dressed in classical Chinese robes, complete with hat, look down benignly upon worshippers. Another formation looks like an old man crouching down.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Then proceed to the Wind Cave which only about 10 minutes drive away. Walking along the platform, you will find this dark-tunnel like cave filled with bats and swiftest. Look around the wall of the cave with torchlight and you might be lucky to spot the bird nest with some eggs in it.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bau</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&ldquo;&rdquo;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&ldquo;&rdquo;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"left\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Tour Duration: Half Day</span></span></strong></p>'),
(137, 'photo/592293fa6521f.jpg', 'PSTT06 Jong\'s Crocodile Farm', 1, ' Half day-Minimum 2pax', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Jong&rsquo;s Crocodile Farm and mini zoo is situated amongst lush tropical fruits trees. This farm is a home to over 1,000 crocodiles as serves as the perfect sanctuary to these fearsome reptiles as they are housed in encloses simulating their natural habitats. Other residents on the farm are sun bear, monkeys, wild boar, mouse deer, leopard cats, monitor lizards, pythons, owls and several others species of birds. Feeding times is at 1100hrs and 1500hrs daily.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">25 3.5 1000 </span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">   </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Tour Duration: Half Day</span></span></strong></p>'),
(138, 'photo/592294b73c17f.jpg', 'PSTT07 Matang Wildlife Centre', 1, ' Half Day - Min. 2 pax', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The Matang Wildlife Centre is about 35KM from Kuching. Located is Kubah National Park, this large enclosed of rainforest is home to some endangered wildlife. Matang Wildlife Centre covers 179 hectares of lowland rainforest with animals in varying stages of rehabilitations. The highlight of the trip is the Orang Utan training programme where young orang utans are being taught or retrained to survive in the wild. These Orang Utans are either orphaned or rescued from captivity. Besides these adorable primates, there is also Borneon Clouded Leopard, Borneon Gibbon, Leopard Cat, Sun Bears, Sambar Deer, Bear Cat and other animals.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">423-42</span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Tour Duration: Half Day</span></span></span></strong></p>');
