(138, 4, 'photo/592294b73c17f.jpg', 'PSTT07 Matang Wildlife Centre', '', '', '', ' Half Day - Min. 2 pax', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The Matang Wildlife Centre is about 35KM from Kuching. Located is Kubah National Park, this large enclosed of rainforest is home to some endangered wildlife. Matang Wildlife Centre covers 179 hectares of lowland rainforest with animals in varying stages of rehabilitations. The highlight of the trip is the Orang Utan training programme where young orang utans are being taught or retrained to survive in the wild. These Orang Utans are either orphaned or rescued from captivity. Besides these adorable primates, there is also Borneon Clouded Leopard, Borneon Gibbon, Leopard Cat, Sun Bears, Sambar Deer, Bear Cat and other animals.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&eacute;&copy;&not;&aring;&frac12;&ldquo;&eacute;&Dagger;&ccedil;&rdquo;&Yuml;&aring;&Scaron;&uml;&ccedil;&permil;&copy;&auml;&iquest;&aelig;&Scaron;&curren;&auml;&cedil;&shy;&aring;&iquest;&fnof;&aelig;&tilde;&macr;&aring;&ordm;&ldquo;&aring;&middot;&acute;&aring;&rsaquo;&frac12;&aring;&reg;&para;&aring;&hellip;&not;&aring;&rsaquo;&shy;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&auml;&cedil;&euro;&eacute;&fnof;&uml;&aring;&circ;&dagger;&atilde;&euro;&sbquo;&aring;&reg;&fnof;&aring;&deg;&dagger;&aelig;&iquest;&rsquo;&aring;&plusmn;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&eacute;&Dagger;&ccedil;&rdquo;&Yuml;&aring;&Scaron;&uml;&ccedil;&permil;&copy;&aelig;&rdquo;&para;&aring;&hellip;&raquo;&aring;&oelig;&uml;&aring;&deg;&eacute;&mdash;&shy;&auml;&frac12;&dagger;&aelig;&mdash;&middot;&eacute;&tilde;&rdquo;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&ccedil;&fnof;&shy;&aring;&cedil;&brvbar;&eacute;&rsaquo;&uml;&aelig;&mdash;&aelig;&circ;&ndash;&aring;&reg;&frac12;&aelig;&bull;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&ccedil;&not;&frac14;&aring;&shy;&eacute;&Dagger;&OElig;&atilde;&euro;&sbquo;&auml;&iquest;&aelig;&Scaro