(140, 4, 'photo/5922963e59e71.jpg', 'PSTT03 Annah Rais Longhouse', '', '', '', ' Half day-Minimum 2pax', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Annah Rais Longhouse still preserved its traditional look. Bidayuh, the second largest ethnic group in Sarawak, is formerly known as the &lsquo;Land Dayak&rsquo; and was once also known as the &lsquo;Engineer of Bamboo&rsquo;. You will be able to see the splendid architecture of their longhouse which was build mostly by bamboo. During the visit, you can view the villagers with their own daily routine like rice pounding and winnowing, basket and mat weaving, bamboo carving and many else. You will be brought into the most unique and important structure, the &lsquo;Baruk&rsquo;, or the head house which is situated in the middle of the longhouse. This once used as a fort to protect the whole village from being attack by enemy. Inside the &lsquo;Baruk&rsquo;, you will be able to view the real human skulls hanging </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">around the fire place in the middle and also their sacred war drum. </span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&aelig;&yen;&aring;&circ;&deg;&aring;&reg;&permil;&aring;&uml;&oelig;&egrave;&plusmn;&aelig;&ndash;&macr;&eacute;&bull;&iquest;&aring;&plusmn;&lsaquo;&aelig;&oelig;&euro;&auml;&cedil;&raquo;&egrave;&brvbar;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&aring;&ndash;&ccedil;&sbquo;&sup1;&aelig;&tilde;&macr;&egrave;&reg;&copy;&aelig;&cedil;&cedil;&aring;&reg;&cent;&auml;&ordm;&dagger;&egrave;&sect;&pound;&aelig;&macr;&rdquo;&egrave;&frac34;&frac34;&aring;&lsaquo;&aelig;&mdash;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&ccedil;&rdquo;&Yuml;&aelig;&acute;&raquo;&aelig;&ndash;&Dagger;&aring;&OElig;&ndash;&atilde;&euro;&aelig;&not;&pound;&egrave;&micro;&egrave;&lsquo;&mdash;&aring;&ccedil;&scaron;&bdquo;&c